1
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:54,280
一天，小秋正在睡觉。
One day, Pelle was sleeping.

2
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:57,200
实际上，天很黑。
It was actually dark.

3
00:00:58,960 --> 00:01:02,560
但是父亲不在那里。
But Father wasn't there.

4
00:01:04,760 --> 00:01:08,280
于是他走到妈妈的床前。
So he went over to Mother's bed.

5
00:01:08,320 --> 00:01:12,640
但是妈妈也不在那里。
But Mother wasn't there either.

6
00:01:12,680 --> 00:01:16,320
妈妈和爸爸在哪里?
Where are Mother and Father?

7
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:33,320
——妈妈!——来到这里。
- Mummy! - Come here.

8
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:47,960
这是你对着它说话的方式Björn。像这样。
This is how you speak into it, Björn. Like this.

9
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:54,320
你会说“妈妈”吗?说“妈妈”。
Can you say "Mummy"? Say "Mummy".

10
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:58,600
不，你把花糟蹋了。
No, you're spoiling the flower.

11
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:14,280
不，不，你不能玩它!
No, no - you're not to play with it!

12
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:28,120
再见，现在去睡觉吧。
Goodbye - off to bed now.

13
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:43,640
1962年11月16日。
It's 16 November, 1962.

14
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:46,280
——你好吗?——嗨,Bjorn !
- Hello? - Hi, Björn!

15
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:48,640
你好吗，亲爱的?
How are you, sweetheart?

16
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:53,280
-也没那么好。——不是吗?
- Well, not all that good. - Aren't you?

17
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:57,400
-妈妈在家吗?——没有。
- Is Mum home? - No.

18
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:31,960
那是1970年2月一个阴冷刺骨的日子。
It's a bitter cold gloomy February day in 1970.

19
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:36,840
电影导演卢奇诺·维斯康蒂正在去斯德哥尔摩的路上。
The film director Luchino Visconti is on his way to Stockholm.

20
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:40,120
电影界最杰出的人物之一，
One of cinema's most outstanding figures,

21
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:43,680
他的艺术和血统都很有名。
he's known both for his artistry and his lineage.

22
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:49,680
他是意大利北部的贵族。他是共产主义者，但他有仆人。
He's from the nobility of northern Italy. He's a Communist, yet he has servants.

23
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:52,680
而且他是公开的同性恋。
And he's openly gay.

24
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:57,680
维斯康蒂出来了，追求纯粹的美
Visconti is out, seeking pure beauty -

25
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:05,240
一个将在他的新电影中扮演主角的男孩身上有完美的美。
perfect beauty in a boy who is to play the lead in his new film.

26
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:12,640
我看不见他的眼睛。它们是什么颜色的?
I can't see his eyes. What colour are they?

27
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:14,920
看这里。
Look over here.

28
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,600
绿色的。
Green.

29
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:20,120
他看起来很可爱——一张漂亮的脸。
He looks lovely - a beautiful face.

30
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:23,720
告诉他拍些照片。
Tell him to take some pictures.

31
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:30,360
多年来，他一直在旅行，在匈牙利，波兰，芬兰，俄罗斯寻找。
For years, he's travelled, searching - in Hungary, Poland, Finland, Russia.

32
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:39,680
在斯德哥尔摩大Hôtel旁边的一间大公寓里
In a large apartment next to the Grand Hôtel in Stockholm

33
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:43,200
一群男孩聚在一起，满心期待。
a group of boys have gathered, full of anticipation.

34
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:46,920
他是个童星。-他是个童星，是吗?
- He is a child actor. - A child actor, is he?

35
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:53,680
你见过你觉得有用的人吗?
Have you seen anyone you think might work?

36
00:04:53,720 --> 00:05:00,000
不,还没有。有些很不错，但我们还没找到靶心。
No, not yet. Some are really sweet, but we've not got a bullseye yet.

37
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:02,920
门就要开了。
The door is about to open.

38
00:05:02,950 --> 00:05:07,360
一个男孩站在门后，还不知道
A boy, stood behind the door, doesn't yet know

39
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:11,560
他的整个人生都将改变。
that his entire life is about to change.

40
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:17,480
他的脸将成为全世界的偶像。
His face is to become an icon - all over the world.

41
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:45,880
他多大了?年长的,对吧?
How old is he? Older, right?

42
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:52,240
-是的，有一点。他是15。——大。15 ?非常漂亮。把你的头。
- Yes, a little. He's 15. - Big. 15? Very beautiful. Turn your head.

43
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:53,920
在概要文件。
In profile.

44
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:59,760
-他在这张照片里很漂亮。-你带照片了吗?
- He's very beautiful in this photo. - Did you bring any photographs?

45
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,520
不。
No.

46
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:04,480
你能绕着房间走一圈吗?
Can you walk round the room in a circle?

47
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:10,400
他是该死的高。
He's damn tall.

48
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:15,880
——漂亮!让他脱衣服。-你能赤裸上身吗?
- Beautiful! Ask him to undress. - Could you bare your torso?

49
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:18,120
——什么?-你能赤裸上身吗?
- What? - Can you bare your torso?

50
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:21,360
-所以你是半裸的——半裸的?
- So you're half-naked. - Half-naked?

51
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:25,880
-也看着摄像机。-看着镜头笑一笑。
- Look into the camera, too. - Look into the camera and smile a little.

52
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:29,600
-很漂亮…-四处走走。
- Very beautiful... - Walk around a bit.

53
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:36,880
让他停下来。拍一个大特写，非常近!
Ask him to stop. Get a big close-up, really tight!

54
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,760
转到相机。
Turn to camera.

55
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:42,840
非常非常接近。四分之三，不是全脸。
Very, very close. Three-quarter shot, not full face.

56
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:50,600
-对着镜头微笑。-对着镜头微笑。
- Smile into the camera. - Look into the camera and smile.

57
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:56,560
-你笑起来真可爱!——谢谢。我们需要拍照。
- You have a lovely smile! - Thank you. We need to take pictures.

58
00:06:56,600 --> 00:07:01,760
马里奥!我们也来拍特写吧
Mario! Let's take close-ups, too -

59
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:06,600
左右侧影，他的脸，和完整的，赤裸的躯干。
profile right and left, his face, and full on, with naked torso.

60
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:11,840
他有一张漂亮的脸。
He has a beautiful face.

61
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:09,120
欢迎来到租户协会。你将有三个选择。
Welcome to Tenants' Association. You'll be given three options.

62
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:11,920
选择最适合你需要的。
Choose the one that best suits your needs.

63
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:16,240
我需要法律建议。
Well, I need legal advice.

64
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:19,800
我该怎么办?我对这些东西一无所知。
What do I do? I know nothing about this stuff.

65
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:24,120
解释一下发生了什么，你需要什么帮助，
Explain what's happened and what you need assistance with,

66
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:27,320
我会尽我所能帮你
and I'll do what I can to help.

67
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:31,720
你可以说我受到了驱逐的威胁…
You could say I'm being threatened with eviction...

68
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:36,880
-…合同终止。——正确的。
- ...with termination of contract. - Right.

69
00:08:39,790 --> 00:08:42,120
在房东的信Björn中，
In the landlord's letter, Björn,

70
00:08:42,160 --> 00:08:46,840
上面说你对其他房客构成了威胁，因为你没关煤气炉。
it says that you're a danger to other tenants, since you left the gas stove on.

71
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:50,600
——这是废话!-当然，但你看这里…
- That's bullshit! - Sure, but look here...

72
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:56,120
-我不是粗心。我每次都检查!-但这都是她担心的
- I am not careless. I check it every time! - But it's all part of her concern.

73
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:59,360
因为一个肮脏的厨房风扇…
Because a filthy kitchen fan...

74
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:04,280
-…被油覆盖，很容易着火。-我知道。
- ...covered in oil, can easily catch fire. - I realise that.

75
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:08,520
这就是为什么你是个危险人物。你必须保持它的清洁。
That is why you are a danger. You have to keep it clean.

76
00:09:09,280 --> 00:09:13,240
现在的问题是解释你为什么躺在床上，
Now, it's a matter of explaining why you were lying on the bed,

77
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:15,840
煤气灶开着。因为她知道。
with the gas burner on. Because she knows that.

78
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:21,240
为什么你不在家的时候煤气灶是开着的。
And why the gas burner is on when you are not at home.

79
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:25,040
你的羽绒被……我把它…
Your duvet... I lifted it...

80
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:29,520
当我把它举起来的时候，它就解体了。
And while I held it up it just disintegrated.

81
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:34,840
它只是坍塌成小小的泡沫橡胶碎片
It just collapsed into little foam rubber fragments

82
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:39,080
老的，恶心的，我不知道是什么。
of old, disgusting, I don't know what.

83
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:43,520
等待……我这里还有个枕头。看!
Wait... I still have a pillow here. Look!

84
00:09:43,560 --> 00:09:45,680
在这下面。看!
Underneath here. Look!

85
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:52,640
虫子就靠这个为生。这太令人恶心了。可怕的!
Bugs have been feeding on this. It's so bloody revolting. Horrible!

86
00:09:52,680 --> 00:09:55,880
在它下面有一层这么厚的…
And under it there was a layer this thick...

87
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:59,880
我甚至不知道…纯粹的污秽。
I don't even know what... Pure filth.

88
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:03,280
它看起来像便便……
It looks like poo...

89
00:10:04,910 --> 00:10:08,200
地毯甲虫或类似的恶心虫子
...from carpet beetles or revolting bugs like that.

90
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,800
该死的恶心!
Bloody disgusting!

91
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:21,640
-我的家对环境有害。——正确的。
- My home's an environmental hazard. - Right.

92
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:23,680
这是真的。
It's true.

93
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:59,040
“旋风”。我的标题是什么意思?
"Cyclone". What did I mean by that title?

94
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:01,520
哇…!
Wow...!

95
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:19,400
我逃离了丹麦那所可怕的寄宿学校
I had run away from this ghastly boarding school in Denmark

96
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:23,640
去了斯德哥尔摩，去了我的外祖父母那里。
and got to Stockholm, to my maternal grandparents.

97
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:29,520
我没有父母，真的。
I didn't have any parents, really.

98
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:33,680
这些都是奶奶照看的。
It was Granny that saw to all this stuff.

99
00:11:34,680 --> 00:11:38,400
她把我的名字写下来做各种各样的事。
She put my name down for all sorts of things.

100
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:41,560
我不知道，我想我只是顺其自然。
I don't know - I suppose I just went along with it all.

101
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:49,520
她想要一个名人给她的孙子。
She wanted a celebrity for a grandchild.

102
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:56,560
我唯一确定的就是我想演奏音乐。
And all I was certain about was that I wanted to play music.

103
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:07,640
我真的不知道这一切有多大。
I didn't really have any concept of how big this all was.

104
00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:13,760
当然，出国是件好事，
It was, of course, great to go abroad,

105
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:15,960
去一个我从未去过的国家
to a country I'd never been to,

106
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:20,000
做一些很酷的课外作业。
to do some kind of cool extra school-holiday work.

107
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:23,160
Ecco -稍微多一点…
Ecco - a little bit more...

108
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,880
请安静!
Quiet, please!

109
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:37,000
塔齐奥——那个漂亮的男孩雕像——
Tadzio - that beautiful sculpture of a boy -

110
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:40,680
由15岁的瑞典男孩Björn Andrésen扮演。
is played by Björn Andrésen, a 15-year-old Swedish boy.

111
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:45,760
当你开始找的时候，你知道自己要找什么吗?
Did you know exactly what you were after when you started looking?

112
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,600
是的,正是如此。就像他。
Yes, exactly that. Just like him.

113
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:53,520
-就像你有照片一样?——是的。他是我试过的第六个男孩。
- As if you'd had a photograph? - Yes. He was the sixth boy I'd tried.

114
00:12:53,560 --> 00:12:55,880
我立刻意识到。
I knew immediately.

115
00:12:55,920 --> 00:13:01,880
他金发碧眼，轮廓完美，灰色的眼睛。你能看见他灰色的眼睛吗?
He is blond, with a perfect profile and grey eyes. Can you see his grey eyes?

116
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:06,440
正如曼先生所写的，“水的颜色”。就像这双眼睛的颜色。
"The colour of water", as Mr Mann wrote. Just like the colour of these eyes.

117
00:13:08,160 --> 00:13:12,760
他应该像雕像一样冷酷。他理解这个角色。他是完美的。
He's to be as cold as a statue. He's understood the part. He's perfect.

118
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:18,160
不会有陷入性行为的风险。那将是一个严重的错误。
There's no risk of slipping into sexuality. That would amount to a serious fault.

119
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:25,280
我正站在维斯康蒂旁边，这时一个金发男孩出现了。
I was standing next to Visconti, when this blond boy turned up.

120
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:28,360
这是显而易见的
It was plain to see

121
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:33,920
维斯康蒂的整个身体都活了过来
that Visconti's whole body came to life.

122
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:42,920
这个男孩长得非常漂亮，长着一张真正上镜的脸。
The boy was exquisitely beautiful, with a truly photogenic face.

123
00:13:44,040 --> 00:13:47,400
他真是个难得的人才。
He was a real find.

124
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:51,880
他是一个有着特殊魅力的男孩。
He was a boy with a very special charisma.

125
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:55,280
他似乎脆弱。
He seems frail.

126
00:13:57,040 --> 00:14:00,160
这在电影里真的很美。
And that's really beautiful in a film.

127
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:09,040
跟那样的孩子打交道你得非常小心。
You need to be very careful dealing with children like that.

128
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:18,040
《威尼斯之死》的故事发生在威尼斯附近丽都岛的一家经典酒店里:
"Death in Venice" is set at a classic hotel on the Lido, an island off Venice:

129
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:20,400
大Hôtel des Bains。
the Grand Hôtel des Bains.

130
00:14:20,440 --> 00:14:25,880
这个故事是托马斯·曼写的，维斯康蒂多年来一直在琢磨。
The story, written by Thomas Mann, had preoccupied Visconti for years.

131
00:14:26,280 --> 00:14:31,160
在这个古老的酒店里，他创造了一个世纪之交的完美环境。
With the ancient hotel, he creates a perfect turn-of-the-century setting.

132
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:37,800
对维斯康蒂来说，《威尼斯之死》是一个深刻的个人故事。
To Visconti, "Death in Venice" is a deeply personal narrative.

133
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:22,000
奶奶也来到了威尼斯。
Granny came along to Venice.

134
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:26,280
她带了一台超级8的电影摄像机，当然，她拍下了一切。
She'd brought a Super 8 cine camera and, of course, she shot everything.

135
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:30,800
维斯康蒂给了她一个小角色，这使她很高兴。
Visconti gave her a small part, which pleased her no end.

136
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:36,920
我还有一个家庭教师——米里亚姆。
I also had a governess - Miriam.

137
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:41,920
她注定要帮助我做功课。
She was meant to help me with my schoolwork.

138
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:47,400
你就像我的弟弟。
You were like a younger brother.

139
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:52,520
我本应该保护他们不受这个新世界的伤害，对我来说也是全新的。
whom I was supposed to protect against this new world, new to me as well.

140
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:55,960
这是我的工作，合同上写的。
That was my job, as stated in my contract.

141
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,880
我发现这很难。
I found it pretty hard going.

142
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:10,960
有人提到维斯康蒂发布了一个命令。
Someone mentioned that Visconti had issued an order.

143
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:15,280
记住，所有船员都是同性恋。
Remember, the whole crew were homosexuals.

144
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:20,880
命令任何人都不许看小塔齐奥。
An order that no one was as much as to to look at little Tadzio.

145
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:29,080
不知不觉中，我在某种意义上被“那个人”保护着。
Without my being aware of it, I was in a sense being protected by "the man".

146
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:38,360
这是一个爱情故事，一个纯洁的故事。
It's a love story, one that's pure.

147
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:41,160
既不是性的，也不是情色的。
It's neither sexual nor erotic.

148
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:44,800
这是一种更高层次的爱。比方说……
It's a higher form of love. Let's say...

149
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:49,880
-爱中的完美。-我想是在找制作人…
- Perfection within love. - I imagine, looking for producers...

150
00:16:49,920 --> 00:16:54,640
一个上了年纪的作曲家和一个青春期男孩之间的爱情故事…
The story of the love between an aging composer and an adolescent boy...

151
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:58,240
